{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think the main memory that I have is at school, really.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were now exclusively Jewish schools and Jewish teachers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was noticeable that every week, sometimes every day, when we got to school in the morning, there would be people missing-- students missing and even teachers missing.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after major raids, major deportations kind of thing, all the classes would have to be rearranged.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was obviously a very sad occasion, every morning, to see that some of your friends had disappeared.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the word was, basically, that people were being sent for resettlement in the East, was the terminology that they used.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't really know about concentration camps, or if we did know about concentration camps-- I mean, our parents probably did know because there were concentration camps even before the war.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Dachau and all that were set up in 1933, so, yes, we knew that there were camps.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was the intention-- to send us to the East.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we had no idea of what was really happening in the camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had no idea of names like Auschwitz and all that sort of thing at that stage.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was just another part of the game.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The whole thing was almost like a game, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That every month there would be yet another restriction, another rule about you couldn't do this, you couldn't do that, and you had to do that and do this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we took it in the way-- we'd had to move from [INAUDIBLE] to [INAUDIBLE], from [INAUDIBLE] to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to go to a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We weren't allowed in the shops.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We weren't allowed to play sports, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And now we were going to be sent to camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
